1
00:00:45,039 --> 00:00:45,679
Well, isn't this

2
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:47,679
the water-reading Fairy Lady?

3
00:00:48,399 --> 00:00:49,000
Come, have a taste.

4
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:52,439
You and I,

5
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:54,679
we're two of a kind.

6
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,320
You want to save Shuisheng,

7
00:00:57,479 --> 00:00:59,399
which means you're colluding with the Communists too.

8
00:01:01,439 --> 00:01:02,679
Oh, Fairy Lady,

9
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:05,239
please don't pin such a big label on me.

10
00:01:05,599 --> 00:01:07,879
I think good kids only do good things.

11
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,760
Whatever Shuisheng has done,

12
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:11,239
I'm willing to save him.

13
00:01:12,319 --> 00:01:13,239
If you want to save him,

14
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,079
you'll have to get past me first.

15
00:01:18,439 --> 00:01:19,000
Hold on.

16
00:01:20,359 --> 00:01:20,560
Come here.

17
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:21,519
You two, step back a bit.

18
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:30,920
So how do we

19
00:01:31,519 --> 00:01:32,319
get past you then?

20
00:01:34,359 --> 00:01:34,719
Old Drunkard!

21
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:35,079
Master!

22
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:35,799
Are you all right?

23
00:01:37,239 --> 00:01:38,000
I got careless.

24
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,319
Didn't dodge in time.

25
00:01:39,319 --> 00:01:40,040
Master,

26
00:01:43,159 --> 00:01:43,840
this round doesn't count.

27
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:45,280
Let's go again, okay?

28
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:49,879
Get down!

29
00:01:49,879 --> 00:01:50,719
Get down, quick!

30
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,680
Don't point that thing at me!

31
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,680
You had this thing? Why didn't you use it sooner?

32
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,040
Master,

33
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,599
I thought you had main character plot armor.

34
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,120
I thought I did too.

35
00:02:07,319 --> 00:02:08,240
Are you out of your mind?

36
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,080
You don't even know who Shuisheng is,

37
00:02:10,159 --> 00:02:11,080
and you dared to agree?

38
00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:12,039
What are you so worked up about?

39
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:13,479
Who is Shuisheng?

40
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:15,080
Sis,

41
00:02:15,479 --> 00:02:17,759
Shuisheng's a key prisoner the Brigadier himself caught.

42
00:02:18,199 --> 00:02:19,599
This man is as good as dead.

43
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,840
How are we supposed to save him?

44
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:21,919
I don't care.

45
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,400
Let me tell you,

46
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,039
you all had a hand in Qiuying's death.

47
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:27,560
If we don't save him,

48
00:02:28,199 --> 00:02:30,560
the Fox Spirit Lady won't let us off.

49
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:32,599
If we save this Shuisheng,

50
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:35,439
then all of us will be freed.

51
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,360
What Fox Spirit Lady?

52
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,280
Someone's just playing tricks.

53
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,479
Reporting in!

54
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:41,319
Speak.

55
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:45,840
What?!

56
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,680
Get out, get out.

57
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:49,240
Yes, sir.

58
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,400
Now what's happened?

59
00:02:53,039 --> 00:02:54,120
Immortal Master,

60
00:02:54,719 --> 00:02:56,000
the ones who smashed the Fox Spirit Lady's temple,

61
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:58,199
they've already been devoured by the Fox Spirit Lady.

62
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:58,800
What?

63
00:02:59,439 --> 00:03:01,319
The Fox Spirit Lady has such a big appetite?

64
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:02,800
This matter...

65
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,039
No, I have to tell the Brigadier.

66
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:04,639
Brother-in-law,

67
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:07,039
the Brigadier's gone off to fight bandits.

68
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:08,400
He's not in Yinyang Ferry.

69
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:09,520
That's right.

70
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,960
That's perfect, then.

71
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,199
What's perfect?

72
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,120
Saving Shuisheng, of course.

73
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:18,680
Chief,

74
00:03:26,599 --> 00:03:27,199
has he confessed?

75
00:03:27,759 --> 00:03:28,280
No.

76
00:03:28,719 --> 00:03:30,240
This guy's like a stone in an outhouse:

77
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,120
stinking and stubborn.

78
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,319
Let him go.

79
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:34,000
Chief Sun,

80
00:03:34,639 --> 00:03:35,240
the Brigadier said

81
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:36,080
without his orders,

82
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:37,560
no one is to take this prisoner away.

83
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,319
The Brigadier gave him three days.

84
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,680
He hasn't confessed after three days.

85
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:43,759
What's the point of keeping him?

86
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,479
Just to make manure?

87
00:03:44,879 --> 00:03:45,280
Yes, sir.

88
00:03:45,319 --> 00:03:45,800
Yes, sir.

89
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:55,879
He's here.

90
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,639
Amitabha.

91
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,080
Shuisheng.

92
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,960
We finally got you out.

93
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:06,039
When you see the Fox Spirit Lady,

94
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,520
be sure to put in a good word for us.

95
00:04:08,879 --> 00:04:09,680
Cut the nonsense.

96
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,039
Since we've already busted you out,

97
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:11,960
hurry up and go.

98
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:19,199
Another job done at last.

99
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:19,879
Yeah.

100
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,000
Now,

101
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,720
I can die in peace.

102
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:28,839
Sis,

103
00:04:30,079 --> 00:04:31,959
Can you really die in peace?

104
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:37,680
Honey,

105
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:39,879
Brother,

106
00:04:40,519 --> 00:04:40,959
You...

107
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,279
Honey,

108
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,000
What are you doing?

109
00:04:45,279 --> 00:04:45,720
Sis!

110
00:04:46,199 --> 00:04:46,720
Brother-in-law!

111
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,120
The Brigadier's prisoner is gone.

112
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,879
Someone has to take the fall.

113
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:51,839
You...

114
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,720
I'll kill you!

115
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:54,680
I...

116
00:04:56,399 --> 00:04:57,120
Honey,

117
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,079
Wife!

118
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:02,040
You beast!

119
00:05:38,519 --> 00:05:39,360
If you don't die,

120
00:05:40,279 --> 00:05:41,639
I can't take your position.

121
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:57,480
Mayor,

122
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,839
let the Brigadier's key prisoner escape.

123
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,160
I had no other choice.

124
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,000
That's why I put duty before family.

125
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,360
I've failed my sister.

126
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,759
I've failed you, Brigadier.

127
00:06:12,519 --> 00:06:13,879
I might as well just die.

128
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:21,560
All right, all right.

129
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,079
Since ancient times,

130
00:06:24,879 --> 00:06:26,480
loyalty and family can't both be served.

131
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,680
You did the right thing.

132
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,319
However,

133
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:30,839
Shuisheng's escape

134
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,639
was a failure on my part.

135
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:36,160
If he escaped, so be it.

136
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,839
He's of no use to me now.

137
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:40,920
Have a seat.

138
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,120
Brigadier,

139
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,879
what did you mean just now?

140
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:55,839
We won a complete victory in this bandit raid.

141
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,360
I captured

142
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,279
one of their key figures.

143
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,920
With him, I can wipe out the guerrillas for good.

144
00:07:05,079 --> 00:07:05,800
Congratulations, Brigadier!

145
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,639
My congratulations, Brigadier!

146
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,639
I'm now a Division Commander.

147
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,480
The commission will arrive in a few days.

148
00:07:16,879 --> 00:07:18,079
Then I'll go arrange it right away.

149
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,279
Yinyang Ferry will celebrate for three days.

150
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,319
There's no Mayor anymore.

151
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:26,839
You

152
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,759
are the new Mayor.

153
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:36,959
Brigadier,

154
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,199
you're like a parent who gave me new life,

155
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:40,759
my father and mother reborn!

156
00:07:46,959 --> 00:07:48,040
It's Division Commander.

157
00:07:48,639 --> 00:07:50,160
Major General, Division Commander.

158
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,720
Yes, Division Commander!

159
00:07:55,439 --> 00:07:56,120
Yes, Division Commander!

160
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,600
Yes, Division Commander!

161
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:58,839
Yes, Division Commander!

162
00:07:58,839 --> 00:07:59,519
We're home.

163
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:00,680
We're home, hang in there.

164
00:08:01,759 --> 00:08:02,519
Qiuying!

165
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,279
Qiuying!

166
00:08:05,079 --> 00:08:05,720
Qiuying!

167
00:08:06,199 --> 00:08:06,800
Qiuying!

168
00:08:08,759 --> 00:08:09,519
Come quick!

169
00:08:09,839 --> 00:08:10,399
Look who this is!

170
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:11,160
Shuisheng!

171
00:08:17,199 --> 00:08:19,079
I thought I'd never see you again.

172
00:08:19,759 --> 00:08:21,560
I thought we'd be parted by death too.

173
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,600
How are you?

174
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,319
I'm fine.

175
00:08:29,639 --> 00:08:31,160
Thanks to Master and Auntie Xiao Ling.

176
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:37,480
No, no, no, don't!

177
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,000
Master,

178
00:08:38,759 --> 00:08:40,000
I can never repay this kindness.

179
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,639
No, no, no.

180
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,559
I'll repay you as your slave in the next life.

181
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:43,960
Slave, my foot!

182
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:44,519
Get up, quickly.

183
00:08:44,519 --> 00:08:45,720
Why do you two love kneeling so much?

184
00:08:45,919 --> 00:08:46,840
Don't ever say that.

185
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:48,799
If you really say you'll be a slave,

186
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:50,440
you'll truly become one in the next life.

187
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:51,240
Come on, get up, get up.

188
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:53,000
Help him sit down, help him sit.

189
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:53,679
Here.

190
00:08:54,279 --> 00:08:54,960
Sit down, sit down.

191
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:56,360
You two talk.

192
00:08:56,879 --> 00:08:58,200
I'll go close the door.

193
00:09:01,799 --> 00:09:02,639
Does it hurt?

194
00:09:04,679 --> 00:09:05,360
Shuisheng,

195
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,200
did you see my parents?

196
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,279
I did.

197
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:14,399
After I left,

198
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,600
I heard two gunshots.

199
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,000
Gunshots?

200
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,279
Then my parents, they...

201
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,240
I suspect it was Lord Beile.

202
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,639
I won't let him off the hook.

203
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,480
Brigadier Li Chuanzhong, for his merits in suppressing bandits,

204
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:43,039
is hereby promoted to Major General Division Commander.

205
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,440
Thank you, Chairman, for your patronage.

206
00:09:50,879 --> 00:09:51,919
Congratulations, Commander Li.

207
00:09:53,679 --> 00:09:54,679
Thank you, thank you.

208
00:09:54,799 --> 00:09:55,879
I have urgent matters to attend to.

209
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:56,879
I must take my leave.

210
00:09:59,279 --> 00:10:00,440
What's the rush?

211
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,080
I've already prepared a banquet.

212
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:03,600
Let's...

213
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,519
have a bite and a drink.

214
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:06,639
Next time.

215
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:07,759
Next time,

216
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,840
when Commander Li is promoted to Corps Commander,

217
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,720
we'll drink together then.

218
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:14,360
Alright.

219
00:10:14,639 --> 00:10:15,200
Then...

220
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,600
I'll take that as a good omen.

221
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,039
Certainly.

222
00:10:17,399 --> 00:10:18,000
Certainly.

223
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:19,440
Dongsheng.

224
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:19,879
Yes, sir.

225
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:20,919
See the guest out.

226
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:22,600
Special Commissioner, this way please.

227
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:27,600
Dongsheng.

228
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,039
Auntie Xiao Ling.

229
00:10:28,039 --> 00:10:28,559
You're looking for me?

230
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,120
Your master needs you.

231
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,440
Hurry home with me.

232
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:31,799
Alright.

233
00:10:31,919 --> 00:10:32,480
Wait for me a moment.

234
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,080
I'll change into casual clothes.

235
00:10:33,879 --> 00:10:35,240
No time to change. Let's go.

236
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,120
Come on.

237
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,240
Master.

238
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:42,039
You wanted to see me?

239
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:45,639
Go to that room.

240
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:46,519
Okay.

241
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:47,399
Just go to that room.

242
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,399
Xiao Lian.

243
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:58,279
Brother.

244
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,159
What are you doing here?

245
00:10:59,679 --> 00:11:00,759
It's dangerous out there now.

246
00:11:00,919 --> 00:11:01,960
They're arresting Communists everywhere.

247
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:04,320
Comrade Zhou Xingbang has been arrested.

248
00:11:04,639 --> 00:11:05,200
What?

249
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:07,240
No wonder.

250
00:11:07,559 --> 00:11:09,279
Li Chuanzhong got promoted from Brigadier to Commander.

251
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:10,840
This time,

252
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,120
the Party sent me to rescue Zhou Xingbang.

253
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,639
Let me go instead.

254
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:19,960
I know the enemy's inner workings better.

255
00:11:27,039 --> 00:11:27,759
Be careful.

256
00:11:29,919 --> 00:11:30,559
Oh, right, Xiao Lian.

257
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:31,960
I'll give you this.

258
00:11:35,679 --> 00:11:36,399
What is it?

259
00:11:36,759 --> 00:11:37,720
My Party membership application.

260
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:48,960
Don't worry, Comrade Dongsheng.

261
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,679
I'll definitely deliver it to the Party.

262
00:11:52,559 --> 00:11:53,679
Then I'd better hurry.

263
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,039
Brother.

264
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:03,919
You must come back alive.

265
00:12:04,559 --> 00:12:05,159
Don't worry.

266
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:15,480
Auntie Xiao Ling.

267
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:16,840
What are you doing?

268
00:12:17,039 --> 00:12:17,559
I...

269
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,080
lost my earring.

270
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:21,360
Isn't it right there on your ear?

271
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:22,480
Really?

272
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,919
I thought I'd lost it.

273
00:12:25,919 --> 00:12:26,480
I was...

274
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,159
Alright.

275
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:27,559
looking for it this whole time.

276
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,200
Nothing's wrong, I'm leaving.

277
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,200
Not staying for dinner?

278
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,240
No, there's no time.

279
00:12:33,279 --> 00:12:33,960
What are you crying for?

280
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,720
I saw it all just now. You hugged him first.

281
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,360
Stop crying, it's all fine.

282
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:39,919
Still crying?

283
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:44,320
Master, I'm leaving.

284
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,039
Reporting, sir.

285
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,320
Come in.

286
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,399
Where have you been?

287
00:12:58,039 --> 00:12:58,919
I've been looking for you all day.

288
00:12:59,279 --> 00:12:59,759
Commander.

289
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,799
I played cards with a few brothers.

290
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,320
How was your luck?

291
00:13:05,879 --> 00:13:06,600
Reporting, Commander.

292
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:09,120
Following the Commander's teachings,

293
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:10,879
to be good to the brothers under me,

294
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:11,879
so...

295
00:13:12,399 --> 00:13:13,080
I lose every time.

296
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:19,639
Commander.

297
00:13:20,159 --> 00:13:21,440
You must have something for me, right?

298
00:13:22,879 --> 00:13:23,480
I...

299
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,399
want to introduce someone to you.

300
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,159
Who?

301
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:29,720
Come in.
